Key fields:

output_path
Relative path to the JSON file where metrics will be written.

log_dir
Directory where log files will be stored.

timeout_seconds
Request timeout per resource in seconds.

warning_response_time_ms
Threshold in milliseconds after which a successful response is treated as warning.

resources
A list of resources to monitor. Each resource needs:

id: unique identifier for the resource

url: HTTP or HTTPS endpoint to check

Example:
json{
  "output_path": "data/sample_output.json",
  "log_dir": "data/logs",
  "timeout_seconds": 5,
  "warning_response_time_ms": 300,
  "resources": [
    {
      "id": "api_server_01",
      "url": "https://httpbin.org/get"
    },
    {
      "id": "db_cluster_02",
      "url": "https://httpbin.org/delay/1"
    }
  ]
}

You can duplicate settings.json and adapt it for different environments if needed.
